name: Jay
description: When I was growing up there used to be a Jay which would frequent our garden, which was quick to fly if it noticed you inside. Jays are the most colourful members of the crow family, and I find myself transfixed by their flash of blue whilst flying and will spend time to watch them when I do see them. | 2592x3888px | f/11, 1/1000s, 300mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 28th May 2021 in Brighton and Preston Cemetery, England
